{"ts": "2026-06-07T20:33:15.384504+00:00", "update": {"tools": {"messages": [{"type": "tool", "data": {"content": [{"type": "text", "text": "{\"number\":1,\"title\":\"DSN with mixed-case password fails to authenticate (works in psql)\",\"body\":\"Hi — running into something odd. We have a service account whose\\npassword contains uppercase characters and a `+` sign:\\n\\n    Password: Service+Acct.2024\\n\\nConnecting with raw psql works:\\n\\n    $ PGPASSWORD=\\u0026#39;Service+Acct.2024\\u0026#39; psql -h db.internal -U svc_user app_db\\n    # connects fine\\n\\nBut via pgcli using a DSN, it fails with \\u0026#34;password authentication failed\\nfor user svc_user\\u0026#34;:\\n\\n    $ pgcli \\u0026#34;postgresql://svc_user:Service%2BAcct.2024@db.internal/app_db\\u0026#34;\\n\\nI url-encoded the `+` to `%2B` per RFC 3986 (since `+` in query\\nstrings means space). pgcli still reports auth failure. If I drop\\nthe special chars from the password it works.\\n\\nMy read of `pgcli/auth.py` is that pgcli parses the DSN with\\nurllib and passes the unquoted password to psycopg, which itself\\nalso does some decoding — possibly the password is being decoded\\ntwice somewhere and the `+` is being interpreted as a space on the\\npgcli side.\\n\\nIs this a known issue with DSN passwords in pgcli? Should I file\\na PR to switch to `urllib.parse.quote(safe=\\u0026#39;\\u0026#39;)` round-tripping?\\nOr is the recommendation to use `~/.pgpass` for special-char\\npasswords and not put them in the DSN?\\n\\npgcli 4.x, psycopg 3.1, postgres 16, Linux.\",\"state\":\"open\",\"html_url\":\"https://github.com/rpnr-bench/T11_R02_C03_A02/issues/1\",\"user\":{\"login\":\"BruceKZ\",\"id\":105292643,\"profile_url\":\"https://github.com/BruceKZ\",\"avatar_url\":\"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/105292643?v=4\"},\"author_association\":\"CONTRIBUTOR\",\"reactions\":{\"total_count\":0,\"+1\":0,\"-1\":0,\"laugh\":0,\"confused\":0,\"heart\":0,\"hooray\":0,\"rocket\":0,\"eyes\":0},\"created_at\":\"2026-05-22T11:15:34Z\",\"updated_at\":\"2026-05-22T11:15:34Z\"}", "id": "lc_6c7d4257-de7d-4fa7-a654-214dabad846e"}], "additional_kwargs": {}, "response_metadata": {}, "type": "tool", "name": "issue_read", "id": "ccd5f12d-dc7c-46f1-a0e1-968cb86fdc88", "tool_call_id": "call_a2026916c1cc4feeae6e5385", "artifact": null, "status": "success"}}]}}}
